WEBVTT

00:04.880 --> 00:12.054
♪

00:13.430 --> 00:19.811
♪

00:23.649 --> 00:25.901
(scream, crashing)

00:25.901 --> 00:27.778
-What's happening?
-I think it's hungry.

00:27.778 --> 00:29.571
I don't know, I--

00:29.571 --> 00:32.366
Honey! My God.

00:32.366 --> 00:34.826
Oh no, no, no! Honey!

00:34.826 --> 00:35.744
♪

00:35.744 --> 00:38.830
(sobbing)

00:38.830 --> 00:48.840
♪

00:56.848 --> 01:00.477
(contained sobbing)

01:00.477 --> 01:10.487
♪

01:16.785 --> 01:19.288
Hurry up and shut the door,
the sun's still out.

01:19.288 --> 01:21.790
I'm coming.
I have a bad hip.

01:21.790 --> 01:23.000
And I have asthma.

01:23.000 --> 01:25.419
but I'll hustle
in an emergency.

01:25.419 --> 01:29.381
It's not an emergency.

01:29.381 --> 01:31.174
It's over.

01:31.174 --> 01:33.677
The baby's gone.

01:33.677 --> 01:35.595
And the mom too.

01:35.595 --> 01:38.557
Just the dad is left.

01:38.557 --> 01:41.601
Dear, I'm so, so sorry.

01:41.601 --> 01:44.813
Will you please make sure
he doesn't hurt himself?

01:44.813 --> 01:46.523
In a minute.

01:46.523 --> 01:48.191
I want to know
what you did wrong.

01:48.191 --> 01:50.193
They got nervous
about the details,

01:50.193 --> 01:52.404
and then she stopped eating.

01:52.404 --> 01:53.864
But the baby,

01:53.864 --> 01:55.449
it kept growing,

01:55.449 --> 01:58.201
and we started
the rope ritual, and...

01:58.201 --> 01:59.953
there was...

01:59.953 --> 02:01.788
there was so much blood!

02:01.788 --> 02:03.165
There's always blood.

02:03.165 --> 02:06.209
Not this much.

02:06.209 --> 02:07.586
Don't be angry with her.

02:07.586 --> 02:09.379
We all make mistakes.

02:09.379 --> 02:12.049
The baby is gone!

02:12.049 --> 02:14.676
Oh, and if you think
I'm angry,

02:14.676 --> 02:16.803
wait till the Foundation
finds out.

02:16.803 --> 02:18.096
They'll think it's my fault!

02:18.096 --> 02:19.598
They're gonna take me
and they'll--

02:19.598 --> 02:21.350
Don't worry, sweetie.

02:21.350 --> 02:24.644
Remember, the Foundation
is a family.

02:24.644 --> 02:26.313
Let me handle this.

02:26.313 --> 02:30.233
You put in the call
and go sit with Dad.

02:30.233 --> 02:32.319
There. Thank you.

02:32.319 --> 02:34.529
This is Lilith.

02:34.529 --> 02:36.323
I'm at Marcia's.

02:36.323 --> 02:39.868
Yes, we need
a complete cleanup crew.

02:39.868 --> 02:42.871
Oh, it's a total cock-up.

02:42.871 --> 02:44.915
She's just upset.

02:44.915 --> 02:46.875
Let's get you
a nice cup of tea

02:46.875 --> 02:50.128
and you can tell me
exactly what happened.

02:50.128 --> 02:53.673
♪

02:53.673 --> 02:58.762
Infertility is a big,
traumatic, multifaceted loss.

02:58.762 --> 03:01.181
Today, the part
we're talking about

03:01.181 --> 03:03.308
is the image you had

03:03.308 --> 03:06.228
of the parent
you thought you would be.

03:06.228 --> 03:08.563
Today's assignment
was to bring an object

03:08.563 --> 03:10.732
that represents that image.

03:10.732 --> 03:13.360
Something you can let go of
symbolically

03:13.360 --> 03:15.862
that might help you let go
emotionally

03:15.862 --> 03:19.282
just a little bit.

03:19.282 --> 03:20.534
Okay.

03:33.380 --> 03:36.091
I didn't have a lot of friends
in middle school.

03:36.091 --> 03:38.677
Um, I was the weird kid
who would knit all the time.

03:38.677 --> 03:42.305
I know you can't choose
what your kids are into...

03:42.305 --> 03:43.932
For our sixth anniversary,

03:43.932 --> 03:46.518
my husband got me
divorce papers.

03:46.518 --> 03:49.938
A letter from a surrogate
we couldn't afford.

03:49.938 --> 03:52.691
I would wrap
my stuffed animals in it

03:52.691 --> 03:54.401
and pretend
they were my kids,

03:54.401 --> 03:55.569
which was insane,

03:55.569 --> 03:57.487
because I was 16 at the time.

03:57.487 --> 04:03.577
It's $186,254.98.

04:03.577 --> 04:05.454
We went bankrupt years ago.

04:05.454 --> 04:09.166
Four miscarriages.

04:09.166 --> 04:10.834
Four.

04:10.834 --> 04:12.252
Bastard has the nerve to say

04:12.252 --> 04:13.920
it's because
I'm working too hard.

04:13.920 --> 04:16.673
Like that would somehow
fix my uterus,

04:16.673 --> 04:18.300
if I just prayed
a little harder.

04:18.300 --> 04:20.677
And every time,
Eric was so great.

04:20.677 --> 04:23.972
I see these women
who are so oblivious

04:23.972 --> 04:25.348
to what they have.

04:25.348 --> 04:28.602
I see my nephew,
my sister's son, and--

04:28.602 --> 04:30.645
I get so jealous.

04:30.645 --> 04:32.564
I feel like--

04:32.564 --> 04:33.690
I feel broken.

04:33.690 --> 04:34.691
Like she let me down.

04:34.691 --> 04:35.942
Like a failure.

04:35.942 --> 04:38.195
I don't wanna be
this angry person anymore.

04:38.195 --> 04:39.613
I know I'm supposed
to move on--

04:39.613 --> 04:41.281
I have to move on.

04:41.281 --> 04:42.908
I know. We have to move on.

04:42.908 --> 04:44.534
At some point,

04:44.534 --> 04:46.495
you have to accept
that the wall

04:46.495 --> 04:48.538
that you keep
banging your head against

04:48.538 --> 04:52.375
over and over and over again
isn't gonna break.

04:55.837 --> 04:59.966
But I can't do it
if he's not...

04:59.966 --> 05:01.593
if you...

05:01.593 --> 05:03.762
If you're not ready
to move on too,

05:03.762 --> 05:05.055
I can't.

05:05.055 --> 05:06.890
You know? It just--
it won't work.

05:06.890 --> 05:11.520
So...So you go, and then,
we can do this together.

05:39.089 --> 05:41.591
(laughter)

05:45.804 --> 05:47.806
This was my grandma's.

05:47.806 --> 05:49.808
(laughter)

05:49.808 --> 05:54.312
She always said
this got her pregnant.

05:54.312 --> 05:56.439
I like that.

05:56.439 --> 05:57.691
She also always said

05:57.691 --> 06:00.819
she thought I would be
a great father.

06:00.819 --> 06:03.113
You guys are all talking
about moving on

06:03.113 --> 06:05.282
and some of you
about how hard it is.

06:05.282 --> 06:09.119
♪

06:09.119 --> 06:10.829
But you all seem to want to.

06:10.829 --> 06:17.335
♪

06:17.335 --> 06:19.462
And I don't want to give up.

06:19.462 --> 06:29.472
♪

06:33.518 --> 06:35.520
And I said, "Eight months
in a submarine or not,

06:35.520 --> 06:37.814
you still have
to wear a condom."

06:37.814 --> 06:40.567
(laughing)

06:40.567 --> 06:43.320
God. I miss when sex was fun.

06:43.320 --> 06:46.698
Not just apps and charts
and tracking and...

06:46.698 --> 06:48.491
Yeah.

06:48.491 --> 06:49.951
Does he still go down on you?

06:49.951 --> 06:51.870
Yeah, but...

06:54.414 --> 06:57.292
You know Eric's still pushing
for another round of IVF?

06:57.292 --> 06:59.252
(softly scoffs)

06:59.252 --> 07:01.254
I'm working double shifts
twice a week

07:01.254 --> 07:03.089
to pay off the last round.

07:03.089 --> 07:04.883
And the marks
on my stomach?

07:04.883 --> 07:07.010
They still haven't faded.

07:13.350 --> 07:15.393
(exasperated sigh)

07:21.775 --> 07:23.985
My cousin just had a baby.

07:23.985 --> 07:26.655
I know, I know; I'm sorry,
but it's a miracle.

07:26.655 --> 07:28.907
-Jesus. Cherise, I don't--
-When she was 21,

07:28.907 --> 07:30.700
she had cancer
and a hysterectomy,

07:30.700 --> 07:32.952
and now she's got
a new baby.

07:32.952 --> 07:35.121
She said some organization
helped her,

07:35.121 --> 07:37.082
and maybe,
if you wanted to,

07:37.082 --> 07:40.168
you can talk to her,
that's all.

07:49.552 --> 07:52.055
(phone ringing)

07:54.516 --> 07:55.850
Hello?

07:55.850 --> 07:57.268
Hey, Susan?

07:57.268 --> 07:59.229
This is Makayla Galiston.

07:59.229 --> 08:02.774
Oh, hey! Cherise told me
you'd be calling.

08:02.774 --> 08:04.484
You guys go way back, right?

08:04.484 --> 08:07.237
Yeah. She was the cool RA
in my freshman dorm.

08:07.237 --> 08:08.655
I bet.

08:08.655 --> 08:12.033
She used to bring me pot
when I was going through chemo.

08:12.033 --> 08:14.869
-Which was for...
-Uterine cancer.

08:14.869 --> 08:16.037
It sucked.

08:16.037 --> 08:17.872
Had the whole thing removed.

08:17.872 --> 08:20.667
Been in full remission
a couple years.

08:20.667 --> 08:22.085
And now you have a baby?

08:22.085 --> 08:24.713
It's crazy, I know.

08:24.713 --> 08:26.381
-That can't be right.
-I swear to God,

08:26.381 --> 08:28.383
the stuff the Foundation can do
is...

08:28.383 --> 08:30.301
(baby crying)

08:30.301 --> 08:31.886
I've gotta go check on Frances.

08:31.886 --> 08:33.680
Let me get you in touch with
the woman who worked with me.

08:33.680 --> 08:34.806
She's awesome.

08:34.806 --> 08:36.391
She'll explain everything.

08:36.391 --> 08:38.059
A miracle worker, really.

08:38.059 --> 08:39.811
Yeah, cool.

08:39.811 --> 08:42.021
-Thanks.
-Of course. Good luck.

08:42.021 --> 08:52.031
♪

09:01.207 --> 09:02.500
-Wait.
-I think--

09:02.500 --> 09:04.043
I think that's all there is.

09:04.043 --> 09:11.092
♪

09:11.092 --> 09:13.678
Do you think it's something?

09:13.678 --> 09:15.889
I don't know.

09:15.889 --> 09:17.182
Cherise wouldn't
have mentioned it

09:17.182 --> 09:21.269
if she didn't think
it was something.

09:21.269 --> 09:23.229
And--and her cousin had--

09:23.229 --> 09:26.983
A hysterectomy,
then a baby.

09:26.983 --> 09:28.401
No, that's not a thing.

09:28.401 --> 09:31.321
I know. That's what I said.

09:33.698 --> 09:35.283
Makayla, I, um...

09:35.283 --> 09:37.994
I thought you wanted
to move on.

09:37.994 --> 09:41.122
And I thought
this is what you wanted.

09:41.122 --> 09:42.832
Thank you.

09:48.630 --> 09:49.798
Hi!

09:49.798 --> 09:52.258
-Hello!
-Hey! Come in, come in.

09:52.258 --> 09:53.676
Oh, yes!

09:53.676 --> 09:55.220
Thanks for coming.

09:55.220 --> 09:57.764
-And you must be Eric.
-Yes, hi, hi.

09:57.764 --> 09:59.474
Ola, right?

09:59.474 --> 10:00.934
That's a unique name.

10:00.934 --> 10:02.727
Oh, my parents were beatniks.

10:02.727 --> 10:04.604
(chuckling)

10:04.604 --> 10:05.814
Would you like
something to drink?

10:05.814 --> 10:07.565
Some water, coffee?

10:07.565 --> 10:10.652
Um, water. Lukewarm, please.

10:10.652 --> 10:13.238
Oh, and an egg, of course.

10:13.238 --> 10:14.572
Right.

10:14.572 --> 10:16.074
Oh.

10:16.074 --> 10:18.284
This is a lovely home

10:18.284 --> 10:24.123
and absolutely deserving
of a child.

10:24.123 --> 10:26.751
The Gravida Foundation
is honored

10:26.751 --> 10:28.503
that you are considering
allowing us

10:28.503 --> 10:31.005
to help you achieve
your miracle.

10:31.005 --> 10:34.259
Please, sit.

10:34.259 --> 10:44.269
♪

10:55.238 --> 10:57.156
Your hands, please.

10:57.156 --> 11:04.539
♪

11:04.539 --> 11:06.583
(exhales deeply)

11:06.583 --> 11:09.544
♪

11:09.544 --> 11:12.630
(chanting in foreign language)

11:12.630 --> 11:22.640
♪

11:26.227 --> 11:29.272
I'm sure you've been
promised miracles before

11:29.272 --> 11:32.025
and you don't believe
that this is real.

11:32.025 --> 11:33.568
But I wouldn't lie

11:33.568 --> 11:36.362
to someone who's been through
what you've been through.

11:36.362 --> 11:41.242
♪

11:41.242 --> 11:43.119
The Gravida Foundation
helped me

11:43.119 --> 11:45.830
when I couldn't conceive.

11:45.830 --> 11:48.041
He's a geneticist now,

11:48.041 --> 11:50.793
and I'm so grateful
that they taught me

11:50.793 --> 11:52.378
how to share their gift.

11:52.378 --> 11:56.090
♪

11:56.090 --> 11:58.343
(peeping)

11:58.343 --> 12:02.388
♪

12:02.388 --> 12:04.599
(Makayla laughs)

12:04.599 --> 12:06.351
It's your egg,

12:06.351 --> 12:08.728
so it's your chick,
if you wish.

12:08.728 --> 12:11.439
If not,
I'll take it for you.

12:11.439 --> 12:14.067
Uh...

12:14.067 --> 12:15.944
you go for it.

12:15.944 --> 12:17.528
(nervous laughter)

12:17.528 --> 12:22.784
♪

12:22.784 --> 12:25.662
That's a little demonstration
the Foundation created

12:25.662 --> 12:29.499
to show off what we can do.

12:29.499 --> 12:33.336
It's not deception
or sleight of hand.

12:33.336 --> 12:36.005
It's magic.

12:36.005 --> 12:40.843
Powerful, old magic.

12:40.843 --> 12:43.262
-So you're a witch?
-Oh no.

12:43.262 --> 12:46.265
I just volunteered to help
after they helped me.

12:46.265 --> 12:47.642
Yeah, of course.

12:47.642 --> 12:57.610
♪

12:57.610 --> 13:02.865
So...how...how does it work?

13:02.865 --> 13:05.284
Well, there's a three-week
cleansing period

13:05.284 --> 13:10.581
with a special diet
and some things you can't do.

13:10.581 --> 13:14.085
And then, I will stay with you
for a week of rituals

13:14.085 --> 13:17.380
to make sure
that the baby is stable

13:17.380 --> 13:20.466
so that you get
the child that you want.

13:20.466 --> 13:25.680
You absolutely deserve
the chance to be parents.

13:25.680 --> 13:28.182
Let me give it to you.

13:31.144 --> 13:33.646
(chick peeping)

13:35.606 --> 13:38.776
That is quite an offer.

13:38.776 --> 13:41.904
Yes. Thank you.

13:41.904 --> 13:44.490
We'll talk about it
and we'll get back to you.

13:44.490 --> 13:46.659
Of course! Take your time.

13:46.659 --> 13:47.910
-Thank you.
-Thank you so much

13:47.910 --> 13:51.039
for having me.

13:51.039 --> 13:53.458
Oh--oh, and here.

13:53.458 --> 13:55.626
Some homemade tea.

13:55.626 --> 13:59.088
Steep it for two minutes
and then add a little whiskey.

13:59.088 --> 14:00.923
Sounds like a party!

14:00.923 --> 14:02.175
Here.

14:04.177 --> 14:06.763
-Take care, now.
-Have a good one.

14:10.933 --> 14:12.643
-Come on, now.
-Oh my God.

14:12.643 --> 14:14.771
I know.

14:14.771 --> 14:17.273
(kettle whistling)

14:21.569 --> 14:23.738
♪

14:23.738 --> 14:25.531
Oh, that's really good.
Want some?

14:25.531 --> 14:27.867
-Really?
-Yeah, yeah.

14:27.867 --> 14:29.535
(he sighs)

14:29.535 --> 14:31.746
♪

14:31.746 --> 14:34.248
-Oh God.
-What? I like it.

14:34.248 --> 14:35.666
It's okay.

14:35.666 --> 14:40.379
All right, fine.
That's more for me, then, mm-hm.

14:40.379 --> 14:42.799
Oh, it's good. Mm.

14:42.799 --> 14:45.760
♪

14:45.760 --> 14:48.471
That thing with the egg?

14:48.471 --> 14:52.517
-That was nuts.
-Yeah. It was a good trick.

14:52.517 --> 14:55.812
Was it a trick, though?

14:55.812 --> 15:00.733
Yeah. It was a good trick.

15:00.733 --> 15:03.152
-But was it really a trick?
-Are you actually considering

15:03.152 --> 15:05.029
she isn't full of shit?

15:05.029 --> 15:06.614
I don't know, maybe...

15:06.614 --> 15:09.242
Look, look.

15:09.242 --> 15:12.120
My grandma tried for 20 years
to have kids.

15:12.120 --> 15:13.704
Twenty years.

15:13.704 --> 15:18.793
And then someone gave her
a carved-stone dick, and bam!

15:18.793 --> 15:20.837
My dad.

15:20.837 --> 15:23.714
Maybe...

15:23.714 --> 15:26.926
maybe this is
our carved-stone dick.

15:26.926 --> 15:29.387
You're drunk.

15:29.387 --> 15:33.224
Compared to another round
of IVF...

15:33.224 --> 15:35.726
what's the risk?

15:35.726 --> 15:38.729
Energy? Hope?

15:38.729 --> 15:40.439
The ability
to look at myself in the mirror

15:40.439 --> 15:42.024
after agreeing
to work with a shaman

15:42.024 --> 15:44.902
who looks like
Cherise's crazy aunt?

15:44.902 --> 15:48.239
Plus, we can't afford
the days off.

15:48.239 --> 15:50.741
If you were pregnant,
we would figure it out.

15:50.741 --> 15:52.410
But this isn't real.

15:52.410 --> 15:56.122
♪

15:56.122 --> 15:57.582
Do you really think
this hippie lady

15:57.582 --> 15:59.417
is a fucking wizard?

15:59.417 --> 16:02.670
♪

16:02.670 --> 16:06.757
Oh! Whoa! Excuse me,
I thought you didn't like it?

16:06.757 --> 16:10.720
It's totally
fucking ridiculous.

16:10.720 --> 16:12.388
I am so sorry.

16:12.388 --> 16:16.267
I had no idea Susan was
so far down the rabbit hole.

16:16.267 --> 16:18.811
It's okay.

16:18.811 --> 16:21.689
It's not as bad as that
pyramid scheme lunch thing.

16:21.689 --> 16:24.317
Um, I made $600 on that,
thank you very much.

16:24.317 --> 16:26.986
Oh! See? Sometimes,
the scam is legit.

16:26.986 --> 16:30.198
Well, it--well, it's
a pretty elaborate scam for,

16:30.198 --> 16:33.659
what you'd say, free?

16:33.659 --> 16:34.827
I know, right?

16:34.827 --> 16:36.996
It's obviously
too good to be true.

16:36.996 --> 16:41.626
I mean, I don't get why
Eric's obsessing about it.

16:41.626 --> 16:47.590
But...what if this one time,
magic is real?

16:47.590 --> 16:50.885
Do you want my actual opinion?

16:55.014 --> 16:56.599
(Makayla sighs)

16:56.599 --> 16:57.975
No, no, no.

16:57.975 --> 17:00.186
Not soft enough.

17:00.186 --> 17:01.395
Get a fluffy one.

17:01.395 --> 17:04.023
Not wool--maybe cotton.

17:04.023 --> 17:05.441
Fleece is nice.

17:05.441 --> 17:06.609
Too much light.

17:06.609 --> 17:07.610
These stay closed.

17:07.610 --> 17:09.695
♪

17:09.695 --> 17:10.655
What are these?

17:10.655 --> 17:11.989
Fertility idols.

17:11.989 --> 17:13.532
The red one
was my grandma's.

17:13.532 --> 17:16.327
She said it helped her,
so I got a few more,

17:16.327 --> 17:17.828
just in case.

17:17.828 --> 17:19.455
Well, it didn't help you.

17:19.455 --> 17:22.500
I can't have their magic
interfering with mine.

17:22.500 --> 17:26.128
They need to be
out of the house completely.

17:26.128 --> 17:28.172
Sounds good.

17:28.172 --> 17:31.217
No cucumber, no shellfish,
no bowling, no smoking--

17:31.217 --> 17:33.469
cigarettes or weed.

17:33.469 --> 17:35.513
Not too much sun,
no liquor.

17:35.513 --> 17:36.931
Red wine is okay,

17:36.931 --> 17:38.975
but just don't go overboard.

17:38.975 --> 17:40.309
And no sex.

17:40.309 --> 17:42.979
But you can masturbate
if you need to

17:42.979 --> 17:45.273
twice a week.

17:45.273 --> 17:46.607
(he sighs)

17:46.607 --> 17:49.026
Makayla, I'll need for you
to text me updates

17:49.026 --> 17:51.237
on your cycle.

17:51.237 --> 17:54.323
Now. You'll have to follow
all of these restrictions

17:54.323 --> 17:56.158
perfectly for three weeks

17:56.158 --> 17:58.577
before the week of the rituals.

17:58.577 --> 18:01.706
If you don't,
the magic won't work.

18:01.706 --> 18:04.834
♪

18:04.834 --> 18:07.253
Oh! Okay.

18:07.253 --> 18:08.629
(clears his throat)

18:08.629 --> 18:13.718
♪

18:13.718 --> 18:15.386
