for your baby, right?

26:35.803 --> 26:37.513
Yeah.
The guestroom.

26:37.513 --> 26:38.722
Eric's old office.

26:38.722 --> 26:40.599
We were gonna convert it
after the baby was born--

26:40.599 --> 26:42.851
Oh no. It needs to be done now.

26:42.851 --> 26:45.604
Preparing the space
is part of the process.

26:45.604 --> 26:46.855
Oh. Okay.

26:51.360 --> 26:53.111
It's all gotta go.

26:53.111 --> 26:54.947
Can we move everything
to the garage?

26:54.947 --> 26:55.948
Not really.

26:55.948 --> 26:57.574
The baby's spirit
needs to know

26:57.574 --> 27:01.703
it will have
a dedicated space of its own.

27:01.703 --> 27:05.374
I'm sure you can
get it emptied by sunset.

27:05.374 --> 27:08.544
Sunset...today?

27:08.544 --> 27:10.087
I don't wanna delay.

27:10.087 --> 27:12.089
Heh. No.

27:12.089 --> 27:15.133
One, two, three.

27:15.133 --> 27:16.260
There we go.

27:16.260 --> 27:17.928
Woo! Ta-da.

27:17.928 --> 27:19.847
Can't believe you guys
are really doing this.

27:19.847 --> 27:20.848
It's your fault.

27:20.848 --> 27:22.307
Thanks for the tip.

27:22.307 --> 27:24.268
You're welcome, I guess?

27:24.268 --> 27:26.728
But I am pulling
for you guys,

27:26.728 --> 27:30.190
despite everything I know
about biology, physics,

27:30.190 --> 27:32.985
science in general.

27:32.985 --> 27:34.653
Oh my God. Is that her?

27:34.653 --> 27:37.364
She looks like my Aunt Marge
who sold us that acid.

27:37.364 --> 27:39.449
Maybe we can get
some good drugs off of her.

27:39.449 --> 27:43.704
Or, uh, you know, a baby.

27:43.704 --> 27:46.290
Either way,
it'll be a trip.

27:46.290 --> 27:48.000
-Really?
-Yeah, yeah.

27:48.000 --> 27:49.418
-Eww.
-Oh, come on.

27:49.418 --> 27:52.170
(door closes)

27:52.170 --> 27:53.797
All right,
let's get going.

27:53.797 --> 27:59.761
