27:59.761 --> 28:01.471
Kneel.

28:01.471 --> 28:06.560
♪

28:06.560 --> 28:10.397
I don't know
why you think I'm joking.

28:10.397 --> 28:13.942
Kneel.

28:13.942 --> 28:15.360
Okay.

28:15.360 --> 28:24.369
♪

28:24.369 --> 28:27.039
We hide the light
of the world away

28:27.039 --> 28:29.917
and invite the light
between the stars

28:29.917 --> 28:35.047
into our homes
and our hearts.

28:35.047 --> 28:36.298
Stay.

28:36.298 --> 28:39.176
♪

28:39.176 --> 28:41.595
(laughing)

28:41.595 --> 28:43.388
You think we'll get a treat
if we're good?

28:43.388 --> 28:45.849
Ruff! Ruff, ruff.

28:45.849 --> 28:48.101
(laughing)

28:48.101 --> 28:54.441
♪

28:54.441 --> 28:55.734
Done?

28:55.734 --> 28:59.112
♪

28:59.112 --> 29:00.656
What?

29:00.656 --> 29:03.158
Take the chicken.

29:03.158 --> 29:05.285
(soft clucking)

29:05.285 --> 29:10.082
♪

29:10.082 --> 29:11.625
Eric, you too.

29:11.625 --> 29:17.339
♪

29:17.339 --> 29:18.715
This bird,

29:18.715 --> 29:21.343
the one hatched
at your table,

29:21.343 --> 29:24.805
represents the child
you did not have,

29:24.805 --> 29:27.849
the one you expected,

29:27.849 --> 29:31.603
the one you will not have.

29:31.603 --> 29:33.438
(gasp, bones crunch)

29:33.438 --> 29:40.070
♪

29:40.070 --> 29:41.905
I'm not hungry.

29:44.408 --> 29:45.993
What are you worried about?

29:45.993 --> 29:47.828
You don't believe
in any of this, remember?

29:47.828 --> 29:52.374
Yeah. 'Cause it's weird
and it's creepy.

29:52.374 --> 29:53.542
But you've bought into it,

29:53.542 --> 29:55.460
so now I need to eat
a bird that died in my hands

29:55.460 --> 29:59.089
in our living room.

29:59.089 --> 30:00.966
Uggh.

30:00.966 --> 30:03.051
I love you.

30:03.051 --> 30:05.554
You're welcome.

30:05.554 --> 30:08.140
Knock, knock!
I'm coming in!

30:09.933 --> 30:12.728
Hey, Mama and Papa,
great to be here.

30:12.728 --> 30:14.646
Who the hell are you?

30:14.646 --> 30:17.149
I'm Dr. Zekeny, OB-GYN.

30:17.149 --> 30:19.693
Yale undergrad, Harvard Med,
Duke residency.

30:19.693 --> 30:20.944
You can call me Dr. Zekeny.

30:20.944 --> 30:23.655
Dr. Z, Doc, Z.

30:23.655 --> 30:25.073
It's all good.

30:25.073 --> 30:26.575
I work at Mercy General
downtown

30:26.575 --> 30:28.368
and I volunteer
with the Gravida Foundation

30:28.368 --> 30:29.911
whenever I can.

30:29.911 --> 30:31.413
My bio's in the app.

30:31.413 --> 30:33.915
It's, uh, nice to meet you.

30:33.915 --> 30:36.793
Likewise, likewise.

30:36.793 --> 30:39.004
And you.

30:39.004 --> 30:40.255
What are you doing here?

30:40.255 --> 30:42.841
He's...helping?

30:42.841 --> 30:44.301
Well, specifically,

30:44.301 --> 30:45.552
Ola makes the magic happen

30:45.552 --> 30:48.472
and I keep you safe
with modern medicine.

30:48.472 --> 30:52.309
Pregnancy's tough,
magic or not.

30:52.309 --> 30:53.685
Uh, if it's okay,

30:53.685 --> 30:55.687
I'd like to get
a quick look-see,

30:55.687 --> 30:57.856
just to make sure
everything's shipshape.

30:57.856 --> 30:59.274
Shouldn't you have done that
three weeks ago,

30:59.274 --> 31:00.567
before we started dieting?

31:00.567 --> 31:01.985
Hon...

31:01.985 --> 31:03.403
Ola would have caught anything
that would have been

31:03.403 --> 31:05.197
incompatible with our process.

31:05.197 --> 31:08.784
This is just for a baseline.

31:08.784 --> 31:10.911
I'll give you a moment to

31:10.911 --> 31:13.413
get changed and, uh,
get on the table.

31:17.334 --> 31:19.086
(Ola chuckles)

31:26.760 --> 31:30.722
Are you okay?

31:30.722 --> 31:33.141
Can you get me a water?

31:36.895 --> 31:38.605
(he clears his throat)

31:55.247 --> 31:57.415
Hey, Eric.

31:57.415 --> 31:58.834
How you feeling?

31:58.834 --> 32:01.419
I'm just having some trouble.

32:01.419 --> 32:03.130
I don't know.

32:03.130 --> 32:06.800
This--this is magic,
and you're a doctor?

32:06.800 --> 32:08.844
How does that work?

32:08.844 --> 32:13.682
Well...we don't know
exactly how Tylenol works,

32:13.682 --> 32:15.267
or penicillin,

32:15.267 --> 32:19.437
but they do,
and so does magic.

32:19.437 --> 32:21.523
I'm a big believer in results,

32:21.523 --> 32:24.442
and the Gravida Foundation
made me,

32:24.442 --> 32:27.612
and I turned out okay.

32:27.612 --> 32:30.991
-So you're a...
-...Foundation baby?

32:30.991 --> 32:32.617
Through and through.

32:32.617 --> 32:35.495
And I'm pretty awesome.

32:40.083 --> 32:43.628
Listen. I know this is scary,
but, uh...

32:43.628 --> 32:46.506
it's gonna be the best decision
you ever made.

32:48.300 --> 32:49.551
You ready?

32:54.598 --> 32:58.393
Yeah, uh, I'll be right there.

32:58.393 --> 32:59.644
(door closes)

33:09.029 --> 33:10.280
(Makayla exclaims)

33:13.116 --> 33:14.117
What's going on?

33:14.117 --> 33:15.994
Oh--cold hands.

33:15.994 --> 33:17.954
You okay?

33:17.954 --> 33:19.539
Yeah.

33:19.539 --> 33:23.168
(door closes)

33:23.168 --> 33:25.670
(she breathes deeply)

33:27.339 --> 33:29.841
(vague abdominal rumbling)

33:32.344 --> 33:35.180
All right.

33:35.180 --> 33:36.973
Before we do the draw,

33:36.973 --> 33:40.143
any family or personal history
of anemia, sickle cell,

33:40.143 --> 33:42.395
cancer, hemophilia?

33:42.395 --> 33:44.606
Any blood disorders?

33:44.606 --> 33:45.857
Nothing on my side.

33:45.857 --> 33:47.192
My grandmother had
breast cancer.

33:47.192 --> 33:50.278
But no history
of leukemia or myeloma,

33:50.278 --> 33:51.821
nothing like that?

33:51.821 --> 33:53.865
No.

33:53.865 --> 33:54.991
Great.

33:54.991 --> 33:57.285
The Foundation will be
very happy to hear that.

33:57.285 --> 33:58.536
Why would they care?

33:58.536 --> 34:00.038
I send them a full report.

34:00.038 --> 34:02.040
It's their process,
they just make sure

34:02.040 --> 34:04.960
I'm not missing anything.

34:04.960 --> 34:07.254
But Makayla, look at him.

34:07.254 --> 34:11.508
His parents, uh...well,
they used the Foundation too.

34:11.508 --> 34:15.220
The Gravida Foundation
is a family.

34:15.220 --> 34:16.471
Welcome.

34:27.983 --> 34:30.652
Your veins are lovely.

34:30.652 --> 34:33.822
Quick pinch.

34:33.822 --> 34:37.158
(she exclaims softly)

34:37.158 --> 34:39.494
Hold that right there.

34:52.507 --> 34:55.593
All right.

34:55.593 --> 34:57.887
Everything looks perfect.

34:57.887 --> 34:59.180
You're healthy.

34:59.180 --> 35:01.099
I'll be back to check on you
every night.

35:01.099 --> 35:02.392
If you need anything
before then,

35:02.392 --> 35:04.352
feel free to call me
on the app.

35:04.352 --> 35:06.313
Oh, and, uh, you're
gonna feel pretty terrible

35:06.313 --> 35:07.605
most of the time.

35:07.605 --> 35:10.609
But, uh,
it's gonna be worth it.

35:10.609 --> 35:13.069
Blink of an eye.

35:13.069 --> 35:14.821
Wouldn't that be something.

35:14.821 --> 35:15.822
I'll let you get changed.

35:15.822 --> 35:17.907
Thank you, Doctor.

35:19.576 --> 35:21.244
(door closes)

35:21.244 --> 35:22.579
Let's begin.

35:22.579 --> 35:26.333
♪

35:26.333 --> 35:28.752
This first ritual
is the true beginning

35:28.752 --> 35:31.338
of your journey into parenthood.

35:31.338 --> 35:35.216
Take your place in front of me,
facing each other.

35:35.216 --> 35:41.681
♪

35:41.681 --> 35:44.351
Huh. That's modern.

35:44.351 --> 35:47.312
Better for my asthma.

35:47.312 --> 35:49.272
It's the ambience that matters.

35:49.272 --> 35:50.815
Speeds things up, anyway.

35:50.815 --> 35:52.233
The mats too.

35:52.233 --> 36:02.243
♪

36:02.577 --> 36:04.579
Blessed be the mother

36:04.579 --> 36:06.831
who gives herself
for her child.

36:06.831 --> 36:11.628
♪

36:11.628 --> 36:13.046
Half.

36:13.046 --> 36:23.056
♪

36:24.808 --> 36:26.101
Blessed be the father

36:26.101 --> 36:28.812
